{"bill":{"bill_id":1671405,"change_hash":"f936a6fd0ddde0aa0c794b831cf7d370","session_id":2021,"session":{"session_id":2021,"state_id":14,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/IN\/bill\/HB1590\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/iga.in.gov\/legislative\/2023\/bills\/house\/1590\/","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-22","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-19","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-19","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-26","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-16","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-22","event":2}],"state":"IN","state_id":14,"bill_number":"HB1590","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":37,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":37,"title":"Various education matters.","description":"Various education matters. Makes various changes to the education law concerning the following: (1) The science of reading and teacher preparation and licensing requirements. (2) The grant for benchmark, formative, interim, or similar assessments with regards to a universal screener that screens for dyslexia. (3) Eligibility requirements for the next level computer science program. (4) Reading deficiency remediation plan requirements. (5) Payments and funding for excess costs of educating certain students with disabilities. (6) The use of funds from the Senator David C. Ford educational technology fund. (7) The fall count day of average daily membership (ADM). (8) Requirements and consequences for violations of the requirements regarding the Indiana diploma with honors designation award. (9) Requirements for public schools regarding adopting or replacing data technology systems. (10) The evaluation of curricular materials by the department of education (department). Requires the department to evaluate, approve, and publish a list of high quality curricular materials in the subjects of science, technology, engineering, and math. Provides that, before curricular material is included on the list, the publisher of the curricular material must entered into a data share agreement with the department. Requires, not later than July 1, 2024, the department to conduct a statewide survey to determine which curricular materials have been adopted for use in certain subjects. Removes a provision that requires choice scholarship schools to conduct random drawings in a public meeting if applicants for enrollment exceed the number of choice scholarships available to the school. Makes provisions for dyslexia screening.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-19","committee_id":1288,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"name":"Education"},{"date":"2023-01-26","committee_id":1307,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"name":"Ways and Means"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-19","action":"Authored by Representative Behning","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-19","action":"First reading: referred to Committee on Education","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-26","action":"Representative Klinker added as coauthor","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-26","action":"Committee report: do pass, adopted","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-26","action":"Referred to the Committee on Ways and Means pursuant to House Rule 127","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-16","action":"Committee report: amend do pass, adopted","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-02-20","action":"Amendment #2 (Behning) prevailed; voice vote","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-20","action":"Amendment #3 (Porter) failed; Roll Call 163: yeas 29, nays 68","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-20","action":"Second reading: amended, ordered engrossed","chamber":"H","chamber_id":37,"importance":0},{"d